ccess_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aInternationally recognized scholars from many parts of the world provide a critical survey of recent developments and achievements in the global field of religious studies. The work follows in the footsteps of two former publications: Classical Approaches to the Study of Religion, edited by Jacques Waardenburg (1973), and Contemporary Approaches to the Study of Religion, edited by Frank Whaling (1984/85). New Approaches to the Study of Religion completes the survey of the comparative study of religion in the twentieth century by focussing on the past two decades. Many of the chapters, however, are also pathbreaking and point the way to future approaches.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aReligionvComparative studies. 0aReligionxStudy and teachingxHistoryy20th century. 4aSchlagworte im Kopf. 7aRELIGION / Religion & Science.2bisacsh1 aAntes, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntes, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBorup, Jørn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDawson, Lorne L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeertz, Armin W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanegraaff, Wouter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHastrup, Kirsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHulsether, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Jeppe Sinding, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoy, Morny M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumar, Pratap, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voca